{"title_page": "List of most expensive non-English-language films", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{More citations needed|date=July 2008}}\nThis is a non-definitive '''list of most expensive non-English-language films''', with budgets given in [[United States dollar]]s. Only films with budgets exceeding US$30 million are listed here. \n\nWhere the source gives the budget in the native currency, conversion is carried out using the exchange rates for the year of release as given by [[The World Factbook]]. In the absence of the exact year the closest year is used instead.<ref>{{citation |title=Field Listings \u2013 Exchange Rates|work=[[The World Factbook]]|publisher=[[Central Intelligence Agency]]}}.\n:*{{cite web|title=2013\u20132017 rates|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/fields/249.html|accessdate=21 January 2018}}\n:*{{cite web|title=2012 rates|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2076.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170907162759/https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2076.html|archivedate=7 September 2017}}\n</ref>\n\n==List==\n{{inc-video}}\n{|cellpadding=\"5\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+List of most expensive non-English-language films\n|-\n! Rank\n! style=\"width:25em;\"|Title\n! Country\n! Primary language(s)\n! Year\n! style=\"width:5em;\"|Production costs (est.)\n|-\n|1\n|''[[Monster Hunt 2]]'' \n|China \n|Mandarin\n|2018\n|$143,000,000<ref name=\"spring festival 2018\">{{cite web|url=http://www.china.org.cn/arts/2018-02/16/content_50543501.htm|title=movie guide for Spring Festival 2018|author=Zhang Rui|publisher=[[China Internet Information Center]]|date=16 February 2018|accessdate=11 March 2018}}</ref> \n|-\n|2\n|''[[Asterix at the Olympic Games (film)|Asterix at the Olympic Games]]''\n|France\n|French\n|2008\n|$113,500,000<ref name=asterix>{{cite web|title=Box Office History for Asterix Movies|work=The Numbers|publisher=Nash Information Services|url=http://www.the-numbers.com/movies/franchise/Asterix|accessdate=21 September 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|3\n|''[[Asura (2018 film)|Asura]]''\n|China\n|Mandarin\n|2018\n|$100,000,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/first-look-chinas-100m-fantasy-adventure-asura-948682|title=First Look: China's $100M Fantasy Adventure 'Asura' (Exclusive)|first=Patrick|last=Brzeski|date=18 November 2016|accessdate=18 November 2016|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|4\n|''[[The Flowers of War]]''\n|China\n|Mandarin, English, Japanese\n|2011\n|$94,000,000<ref name=\"statista-china (June 2013)\">{{cite web|title=Most expensive film productions in China and Hong Kong as of June 2013 (in million U.S. dollars)|date=June 2013|publisher=[[Statista]]|url=http://www.statista.com/statistics/260159/most-expensive-film-productions-in-china/|accessdate=27 November 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n|5\n|''[[2.0 (film)|2.0]]''\n|India\n|Tamil\n|2018\n|{{H:title|Converted at the 2017 exchange rate of 65.17 INR to 1 USD|<!-- DO NOT ALTER THE FIGURE USED HERE. EXCHANGE RATES FLUCTUATE DAILY AND FOR THIS REASON THIS ARTICLE USES THE AVERAGE ACROSS THE WHOLE OF 2017 WHICH IS THE MOST RECENT YEAR DATA EXISTS FOR. -->$87,500,000}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/kamal-haasans-indian-2-finally-shelved-due-budget-issues-793369|title=Kamal Haasan's Indian 2 finally shelved due to budget issues?|last=Upadhyaya|first=Prakash|date=2019-03-07|website=International Business Times, India Edition|language=english|access-date=2019-08-08}}</ref>\n|-\n|6\n|''[[The Monkey King 3]]'' \n|Hong Kong, China \n|Mandarin\n|2018\n|$87,300,000<ref name=\"spring festival 2018\" />\n|-\n|7\n|''[[Red Cliff (film)|Red Cliff]]''\n|China\n|Mandarin\n|2008\n|$80,000,000<ref name=\"statista-china (June 2013)\" />\n|-\n|8\n|''[[Asterix and Obelix: God Save Britannia]]''\n|France\n|French\n|2012\n|$77,600,000<ref name=\"asterix\" />\n|-\n|9\n|''[[D-War II: Mysteries of the D