rmula 1\u2019s new regulations delayed until 2022|first=Daniel|last=Herrero|work=[[Speedcafe|speedcafe.com]]|publisher=[[Speedcafe]]|date=20 March 2020|accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Initial design ==\nThe car was designed by David Worner and Jonathan Carter, both of whom are in their first year in the team having previously worked with [[Red Bull Racing|Red Bull]] and [[Renault in Formula One|Renault]] respectively.<ref name=\"designer\" /> Williams have described the FW43 as being an evolution of its predecessor, believing the [[Williams FW42|FW42]] was a good basis on which to design the FW43.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.williamsgpnews.com/news/fw43-will-be-an-evolution-of-williams-2019-car/|title=FW43 will be an evolution of Williams\u2019 2019 car|date=2019-07-10|website=Williams Grand Prix News|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n\nSeveral major changes were made regarding the [[Sidepod|side pods]]. Firstly the car introduced a steep slope from the top of the side pod to the floor to as to encourage the air to reach the floor of the car. This has drawn parallels with the side pod designs seen on the [[Red Bull RB8]] and [[Sauber C31]] seen in {{F1|2012}}. Williams have also reduced the size of the air inlets on the front of the side pods and have flattened the outer surface of the side pod. The wing mirror and wing mirror supports have also seen aerodynamic refinement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/williams-tech-insight-new-fw34/4687674/|title=Tech insight: Can Williams rise again with its new FW43?|last=Somerfield|first=Matthew|last2=Piola|first2=Giorgio|date=18 February 2020|website=motorsport.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== Pre season testing ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\nAfter experiencing their worst season in the team's history, including missing the first two days of pre-season testing in 2019, testing for the 2020 season went much more smoothly for Williams. George Russell was the first car out on track on the first day of the test, and the team completed 737 laps over the shortened 6 days of testing. The FW43's fastest lap time of the test, achieved by George Russell on the final day of running on the C5 tyre, was also over 2.2 seconds quicker than the time that he achieved in the previous year's FW42 during qualifying for the 2019 Spanish Grand Prix. \nNonetheless, after pre-season testing Russell commented that he believed that Williams still had the slowest car (after the team finished last in the [[2019 Formula One World Championship|preceding season]]).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/148493/russell-williams-still-has-the-slowest-car|title=Russell believes Williams Formula 1 team still has the slowest car|last=Karpov|first=Oleg|last2=Codling|first2=Stuart|date=29 February 2020|website=Autosport.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-02}}</ref>\n\n== Complete Formula One results ==\n([[Template:F1 driver results legend 5|key]])\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%\"\n!Year\n!Entrant\n!Power unit\n!Tyres\n!Driver name\n!Car no.\n! colspan=\"11\" |Grands Prix\n!Points\n!WCC pos.\n!Ref.\n|-\n! rowspan=\"8\" |{{F1|2020}}\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[ROKiT Williams Racing]]\n| rowspan=\"8\" |[[Mercedes AMG High Performance Powertrains|Mercedes]] M11 EQ Performance\n| rowspan=\"8\" |{{Pirelli}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Nicholas Latifi]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" |6\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Dutch Grand Prix|NED]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Spanish Grand Prix|ESP]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Monaco Grand Prix|MON]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|AZE]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Canadian Grand Prix|CAN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 French Grand Prix|FRA]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Austrian Grand Prix|AUT]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 British Grand Prix|GBR]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Hungarian Grand Prix|HUN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Belgian Grand Prix|BEL]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Italian Grand Prix|ITA]]<br>\n! rowspan=\"8\" | 0*\n! rowspan=\"8\" | &ndash;*\n| rowspan=\"8\" align=\"center\" |\n|-\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Singapore Grand Prix|SIN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Russian Grand Prix|RUS]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Japanese Grand Prix|JPN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 United States Grand Prix|USA]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Mexico City Grand Prix|MEX]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Brazilian Grand Prix|BRA]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|ABU]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Australian Grand Prix|AUS]]<sup>\u2021</sup><br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Bahrain Grand Prix|BHR]]<sup>\u2021</sup><br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Chinese Grand Prix|CHN]]<sup>\u2021</sup><br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Vietnamese Grand Prix|VIE]]<sup>\u2021</sup><br>\n|-\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|- style=\"border-top:2px solid #aaaaaa\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" |[[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" |63\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Dutch Grand Prix|NED]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Spanish Grand Prix|ESP]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Monaco Grand Prix|MON]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|AZE]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Canadian Grand Prix|CAN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 French Grand Prix|FRA]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Austrian Grand Prix|AUT]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 British Grand Prix|GBR]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Hungarian Grand Prix|HUN]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Belgian Grand Prix|BEL]]<br>\n| style=\"background:#\"|[[2020 Italian Grand Prix|ITA]]<br>\n|-\n|\n|\n|\n|\